Navigate to other release versions of Doxee Platform Resource Explorer

[6.6](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/resource-explorer-6-6)

[6.7](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/resource-explorer-6-7)

The screenshot below shows Resource Explorer after the first start:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The application window is divided into three main parts:

- At the top, there is the menu bar, together with the address field and the action icons.

- Below, there is the tree view on the left and the content pane on the right.

The tree view allows you to navigate your folders. The local file system is available right away.

Any remote servers that you connect to will appear under "Registered Hosts".

## Connecting to WebDAV Servers
Right-click "Registered Hosts", click "Configure Hosts".

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The "Hosts" dialog opens. Click "Add".

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The "Add Host" dialog opens.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Enter a label and the URL of the server. If you are unsure about the exact URL, you can try it in a browser until you get it right.

You can also specify a user name and a password in this dialog, in case your server requires them. If you leave them blank, you may be prompted for authentication later.

All hosts that you configure appear in the list of the "Hosts" dialog.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

There you can edit or delete them. Click "OK" when you are done. The newly registered connections appear under the "Registered Hosts" node in the tree.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Multiple Tabs
You can open more tabs by clicking the "New Tab" button ![](data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABIAAAAQCAIAAACUZLgLAAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAAARnQU1BAACxjwv8YQUAAAAJcEhZcwAADsMAAA7DAcdvqGQAAABySURBVDhPpcvdCYAgGIVhh7Jt0l3KRonswjUCHaTov0aI4BAlInz5XB04vMz8cmcnEbKDKC3biZBtRMhWImRLgKsy2WL7kM0BTnGpsX3IpjerOPsQGs8D2RhgSy4abB+yIaAreF5j+yJZDLKeKC0jM+YCxRrRYNFhh30AAAAASUVORK5CYII=) on the top right edge of the content pane. The tabs allow you to switch between several different locations quickly and easily.

## Home Directory
The "Home" button ![](data:image/png;base64,) navigates to the home directory on the current connection (local file system or the Doxee Content Repository).
